  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "Once a bottle of white wine has been opened, it generally lasts about 3 to 5 days if stored properly. To extend its freshness, you should reseal the bottle with a cork or a wine stopper and store it in the refrigerator. Some white wines, particularly those with higher acidity or residual sugar, might last a little longer, but it's always best to check for any changes in taste or aroma to determine if it is still enjoyable to drink.",
